headline: Dollar General Stock Just Popped, but Is the Worst Really Behind It?
summary: Dollar General is starting to benefit from more affluent customers trading down on their shopping choices.  Dollar General (NYSE: DG) has struggled in recent years, as inflationary pressures hurt its lower-income consumer base.  Is Dollar General turning the corner?
